    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-08T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-08T11:00:00-05:00" n="110"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/734: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sparks</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-08T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 8, 1941—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>241. President Lescot with the unanimous approval of the permanent Committee of
                    National Assembly declared war on Japan.</p>
                <p>A state of siege has been declared and warning has been served that any saboteur
                    will be tried by court martial and executed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sparks</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
